(tools/build_static_kpathsea.sh) and, from 0.7.4, on Windows (the `kpathsea_sys`
crate's `build_from_source`). On platforms where no library is available
(notably macOS/MacTeX, and MiKTeX hosts) the binary instead calls the host's
`kpsewhich` executable as a subprocess, and no kpathsea code is linked in.

